{
  "stem": "7832.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "See, my finger was-- the nail came off and my-- my whole finger was like a pretzel.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was like, leaning on this finger for years after I came out of the camp.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And with-- with massaging and therapy and all of that, it-- it's-- it's OK, but it's still-- it'll never be what this one is.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so that was the second experiment that we lived through, the five of us.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this one girl, her name was Sabka, and she was Polish, and she came into Auschwitz in 1943.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They caught her.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She was in hiding, and they caught her, and they brought her into Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You want me to tell you what happened to her?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "How she wound up, or just you want me to tell my relationship with her?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Your relationship.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK, well she came into Auschwitz in 1943, and in 1944, she was selected for the experiments, and we were together.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But she was already-- she was six years older that I was.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She was 19 years old when we met.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she was at Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She was already in the war for six years, in hiding and in ghettos and then in-- in the camps.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So she was a little bit more wiser to the situation.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so it was good, because she-- she was very-- she-- she-- she conditioned herself to the-- to the situation, and she was like my support.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She was, like, helping me to deal with all these atrocities and the experiments, especially.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were the worst.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so when we got to the third experiment, we were-- we kind of-- we took the-- the chance of talking to each other a little bit more.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And she said, it's OK.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I think so.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
